Let's determine the monthly rate we will use to calculate the monthly payment.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &=\dfrac{0.052}{12}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{0.43\%}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the monthly rate of the mortgage is 0.43%.

Let's now determine the balloon payment.

$$ \begin{aligned}
PVA &= \$12,846.10 \times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.0043\right)^{264}}}{0.0043}
\\[10pt]
&= \$12,846.10 \times\dfrac{0.677859114}{0.0043}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$ 2,025,080.46}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the balloon payment on the eight-year of a 30-year mortgage is $2,025,080.46.**
